    <stitle>SINGLE SPEED REAR AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - ASSEMBLE - DIFFERENTIAL ( Figure 45 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400845">Figure 45</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1400845" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400845" filename="../figg14/g1400845.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Differential - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If ring gear was removed from differential case, re-install at this time. Clean mating
                surfaces and bolt ring gear to differential case in two places, 180 degrees apart to help eliminate ring
                gear runout. Use hydraulic press and suitable riveting fixture (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400846">Figure 46</hotlnk>). Pressure requirement per rivet is 45 to 50 U.S. tons (41
                to 45 metric tons).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400846" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400846" filename="../figg14/g1400846.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Use Hydraulic Press</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Ring gear and pinion must be replaced as a matched set only.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para></para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bearing cones to differential case halves. Place bearing cups on cones during
                remainder of assembly to prevent damage to bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400847">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400847" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400847" filename="../figg14/g1400847.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Bearing Cups On Cones</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use of press and proper adapter is preferred to eliminate possible damage to bearings.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a small amount of gear lubricant to all mating surfaces. This will aid in assembly by
                keeping parts together and providing initial lubrication.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place thrust washer and side gear in left hand differential case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400848">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400848" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400848" filename="../figg14/g1400848.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Left Hand Differential Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble differential pinions and thrust washers on cross shaft. Place assembly in left hand
                differential case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400849">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400849" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400849" filename="../figg14/g1400849.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Differential Pinions &#38; Thrust Washers</caption>
            </figure>
            <para></para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place remaining side gear and thrust washers in position on differential pinions (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400850">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400850" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400850" filename="../figg14/g1400850.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Side Gear &#38; Thrust Washers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble case halves, making sure match marks are lined up (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400851">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400851" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400851" filename="../figg14/g1400851.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Assemble Case Halves</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install differential case bolts and nuts; tighten alternately and evenly. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s14008t_30.xml" xrefid="hl1400805">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>, for proper fastener torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400852">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400852" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400852" filename="../figg14/g1400852.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Differential Case Bolts &#38; Nuts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
